[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = Traplana","category":"page"},{"location":"#Traplana","page":"Home","title":"Traplana","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for Traplana.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [Traplana]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Traplana.cos_step-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"Traplana.cos_step","text":"cos_step(t;p=1, center=true)\n\nCosine-based step function\n\nf(t) = (1-cos(pipt))\n\nTime t \\in [0,1]\nParameter p sets steepness. Choose p=1 or p>1.\n\nIf p>1 then the step function is centered to have f(0.5)=0.5. To avoid this choose center=false.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> cos_step(0.5)\n0.5\n\njulia> cos_step(0.4;p=2)\n0.2061073738537635\n\njulia> cos_step(0.4;p=2, center=false)\n0.9045084971874737\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Traplana.cos_step_der-Tuple{Any, Integer}","page":"Home","title":"Traplana.cos_step_der","text":"cos_step_der(t,n :: Integer;p=1, center=true)\n\nDerivatives of cosine-based step function.\n\nNumber of derivatives n, must be an Integer. \n\nExamples\n\njulia> cos_step_der(0.1,3;p=2, center=false)\n3-element Vector{Float64}:\n1.8465818304904567\n15.96935537647813\n-72.90012864472101\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Traplana.eulerian_triangle-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"Home","title":"Traplana.eulerian_triangle","text":"eulerian_triangle(n::Int64, k::Int64)\n\nComputes the Eulerian number of the Eulerian triangle.\n\nSee also: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eulerian_number\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Traplana.tanh_step-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"Traplana.tanh_step","text":"tanh_step(t;p=5)\n\nTanh-based step function\n\nf(t) = (1 + tanh(p(t - 05)))2\n\nTime t \\in [0,1]\nParameter p sets steepness.\n\nInitial and terminal value f(0)=0 and f(1)=1 are approached, and can not be reached exactly. To reach f(1)>0.99 choose parameter p>4.6.  \n\nExamples\n\njulia> tanh_step(0.5)\n0.5\n\njulia> tanh_step(0.4;p=10)\n0.11920292202211757\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Traplana.tanh_step_der-Tuple{Any, Integer}","page":"Home","title":"Traplana.tanh_step_der","text":"tanh_step_der(t,n :: Integer;p=1)\n\nDerivatives of tanh-based step function.\n\nNumber of derivatives n, must be an Integer. \n\nExamples\n\njulia> tanh_step_der(0.1,3;p=10)\n3-element Vector{BigFloat}:\n 0.00670475341512948540267924357749507180415093898773193359375\n 0.1340051307052893501270622106185563061489978404668007613377242087398415800597595\n 2.676506919848872478504524070795339666523688433093212247964472721213141447181446\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
